R(x,y)\le \binom{x+y}y n.
x=0
y=0
0\le x+y\le n
x+y=n+1
x,y>0
R(x,y)\le R(x-1,y)+R(x,y-1) \le \binom{x+y-1}y n +\binom{x+y-1}{y-1} n=\binom{x+y}y n.
\binom21=2
\binom42=6
\binom63=20
\binom84=70
